  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Chronic endometritis is a persistent inflammation of the endometrium. Chronic endometritis is
      asymptomatic or little symptomatic. Sometimes, patient with chronic endometritis can have
      genital bleeding, pelvic chronic pain, pain during sexual relations, persistent vaginal white
      loosing. The hysteroscopy can detect the presence or absence of chronic endometritis.

      Some studies showed that the endometritis could have an impact on the embryo implantation and
      could explain recurrent miscarriages or repeated embryo implantation failures.

      The goal of this study is to evaluate the frequency of the chronic endometritis in patients
      with recurrent miscarriages or repeated embryo implantation failures
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
